<paragraph blockId="12.[264,1325,505,1411]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis box="[312,414,1305,1330]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[431,620,1305,1330]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Varta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrofasciata">
<emphasis box="[431,620,1305,1330]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">V. rubrofasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[681,854,1305,1330]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Varta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrostriata">
<emphasis box="[681,854,1305,1330]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">V. rubrostriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resemble each other externally but can be readily distinguished by the characters of the male genitalia given in the key. Aedeagal shaft in this species is very strongly sinuate.
</paragraph>
